The paper deals with synthesizing novel views of complex scenes using deep neural networks. This involves computer vision (CV) techniques such as image synthesis and view synthesis, which are covered under cs.CV. The paper also deals with representing scenes using neural networks, which falls under the category of machine learning (ML) and artificial intelligence (AI), covered under cs.LG and cs.AI. The paper also deals with rendering techniques for complex geometry and appearance, which falls under computer graphics (CG), covered under cs.CG. Finally, the paper deals with optimizing neural networks, which is a common theme in many sub-categories of computer science, but given the focus on CV and ML techniques, cs.CV and cs.LG are the most likely sub-categories.
